  "Stratosphere, where ozone absorbs UV radiation and warms the air": "",
  "Mesosphere, where meteors burn up": "",
  "At around 11 km, the aircraft crosses the tropopause into the stratosphere, where the absorption of ultraviolet radiation by ozone causes temperatures to increase with altitude instead of decreasing.": "",
  "During a sunset, the sky turns orange and red instead of blue. This happens because:": "",
  "Sunlight passes through a much thicker layer of atmosphere at low angles, scattering away most blue light and allowing longer red and orange wavelengths to reach the observer": "",
  "Earth's rotation changes the spectrum of visible light at dusk within the typical range of values": "",
  "The Sun emits more red light in the evening, particularly regarding shorter following the established framework": "",
  "Pollution in the lower atmosphere absorbs all blue light under equilibrium conditions": "",
  "At sunset, sunlight must travel through a much longer path through the atmosphere, and Rayleigh scattering removes most of the shorter blue wavelengths along the way, leaving the longer red and orange wavelengths to dominate what we see.": "",
  "A weather balloon launched from a research station measures a temperature of negative 55 degrees Celsius at 12 km altitude, then negative 50 degrees Celsius at 15 km. This temperature increase indicates the balloon has:": "",
  "Descended back to a lower altitude without the researchers noticing": "",
  "Entered the mesosphere where temperatures fluctuate randomly": "",
  "Passed through the tropopause into the stratosphere where ozone absorption warms the air": "",
  "Malfunctioned and is giving inaccurate readings": "",
  "The reversal from cooling to warming indicates the balloon has crossed the tropopause into the stratosphere, where ozone molecules absorb ultraviolet radiation and convert it to heat, causing temperatures to rise with increasing altitude.": "",
  "A greenhouse on a farm works on a similar principle to the atmospheric greenhouse effect. In both cases, the key mechanism is that:": "",
  "Convection currents are created that distribute heat evenly": "",
  "Visible light is blocked from entering the system": "",
  "Visible light enters and is absorbed, but the re-emitted infrared energy is partially trapped, causing warming": "",
  "Wind is prevented from carrying heat away from the surface": "",
  "In both a physical greenhouse and Earth's atmosphere, incoming visible light passes through (glass or the atmosphere), is absorbed by surfaces inside, and re-emitted as infrared radiation that is then partially trapped (by glass or greenhouse gases), raising the internal temperature.": "",
  "A satellite in low Earth orbit experiences significant atmospheric drag at 300 km altitude but almost none at 800 km. This is because at 800 km the satellite is in the:": "",
